poker

Class HumanPokerPlayer

  • java.lang.Object
    • poker.PokerPlayer
      • poker.HumanPokerPlayer

  • public class HumanPokerPlayer
extends PokerPlayer
    An subclass of PokerPlayer that allows for human interaction and user input. The input used from the TwitterStream attribute determines the actions taken during a round of poker.
    Author:
    Dara Callinan, Jazheel Luna, Eoghan O'Donnell, Crischelle Pana

    • Method Detail

      • getTwitterInput

        private java.lang.String[] getTwitterInput()
        Retrieves and parses input from the TwitterStream attribute. The input is broken down into an array of words, where Twitter '@' strings and punctuation are removed.
        Returns:
        An array of words from the input string.
        See Also:
        TwitterStream.parseResponse()
